    <item>
      <title>Continual Learning @ IJCNN 2020 </title>
      <link>https://AndreaCossu.github.io/post/ijcnn2020-paper/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2020 10:01:42 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>https://AndreaCossu.github.io/post/ijcnn2020-paper/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Our new paper &lt;em&gt;Continual Learning with Gated Incremental Memories for Sequential Data Processing&lt;/em&gt; has been accepted for presentation at &lt;a href=&#34;https://wcci2020.org/&#34;&gt;IJCNN 2020&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;
Gated Incremental Memory is a progressive Recurrent Neural Network which is able to learn multiple incoming tasks while at the same time mitigating forgetting of previous knowledge.&lt;br&gt;
It is a joint work together with &lt;a href=&#34;http://pages.di.unipi.it/bacciu/&#34;&gt;Davide&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;http://pages.di.unipi.it/carta/&#34;&gt;Antonio&lt;/a&gt;. Yay 😃&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
